id: pm-pxx0
title: Implement local telemetry queue retention_days TTL cleanup
description: retention_days exists in telemetry settings but no cleanup logic prunes old queue entries or events from disk.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: "audit:2026-04-26",pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T14:52:27.856Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-27T19:45:25.713Z"
deadline: "2026-05-10T14:52:27.856Z"
author: audit-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: Stale queue entries older than retention_days are pruned during flush cycles.
parent: pm-lnq3
resolution: Local telemetry runtime now prunes stale queue entries older than telemetry.retention_days during flush cycles.
expected_result: Queue entries older than retention_days are removed while fresh entries continue normal export/retry flow.
actual_result: "flushQueue prunes stale entries pre-send, rewrites queue with retained entries, and regression tests confirm stale entries are omitted from export while targeted suites pass."
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:27:52.897Z",codex-agent,"Wave kickoff 2026-04-27: baseline captured via pm context/list-open telemetry snapshot; item claimed and moved to in_progress. After remote telemetry fixes, local runtime update will implement retention_days TTL pruning during flush in src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts with focused unit coverage and architecture docs alignment. Evidence logs linked under scripts/prod/telemetry baseline and pm-pxx0 execution log."
  "2026-04-27T19:43:04.342Z",codex-agent,"Implementation 2026-04-27: updated src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts to prune stale queue entries by telemetry.retention_days before due/retry processing. flushQueue now rewrites queue after pruning and reports post-prune queue size; telemetry command context carries retention_days so start/finish flush cycles apply deterministic retention behavior."
  "2026-04-27T19:43:07.208Z",codex-agent,"Verification 2026-04-27: pnpm build passed and node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts passed (9 tests), including new stale-entry pruning regression that confirms aged queue events are excluded from export payload and removed from local queue during flush."
  "2026-04-27T19:44:44.239Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence 2026-04-27: local targeted suites passed (telemetry runtime + health command, 34 tests). retention_days flush pruning regression confirms stale queue entries are excluded from export and removed from queue rewrite path."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:43:10.782Z",codex-agent,Local retention pruning is intentionally timestamp-based on event.occurred_at and only removes entries older than retention cutoff; invalid/missing timestamps are preserved to avoid accidental data loss from malformed local rows.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:43:14.280Z",codex-agent,Retention controls should apply where backlog forms (local JSONL queue) in addition to downstream storage cleanup; this keeps disk growth bounded even when remote delivery is delayed.
